rooms.Name: Daxx and Jahana's nookie place.
rooms.Description:
Before you, in all it's splendor, is a room with everything a newlywed
couple could want on their wedding night...a king sized bed, lots of 
pillows, whipped cream, baby oil, a riding crop, etc...etc...etc...<G>
Oh yeah, and don't forget the 6 dozen red rose petals scatted on the
bed.  The room is lit low and there's some Luther Vandross playing on
the stereo {did you expect Mortal Kombat, maybe?}.  The whole room just
screams, "MAKE LOVE IN ME!!!!"

rooms.Name: Rich driveway
rooms.Description:
You are standing in the middle of a posh driveway lined with rich ferns
and expensive flowers.  Beauty surrounds you as you gaze at the full, green
grass and the rolling hills.  A pair of pillars beckon you inside and on one
is written the word "Bushwood".  There is a plaque on the other pillar.

ExtraDescs.Description:
+-----------------------+
   |    Caddyshack Zone    |
   | Completed May 3, 1996 |
   | by Stretch and Teddy  |
   +-----------------------+

rooms.Name: Speed bump
rooms.Description:
The rich driveway continues to wind its way through the country club estate.
The speedbump is here to keep hooligans from tearing through the parking lot
like a bunch of maniacs.  Obviously, it doesn't work

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
From here you can see the vast expanse of the parking lot.  Looking south,
the driveway beckons you with its splendor.  The lot is filled with all kinds
of insanely expensive cars; BMW's, Mercedes, Lexus, Yugos...You can only hope
to someday own a vehicle as nice as these.

rooms.Name: Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
You are in the south-west corner of the parking lot.  From here you can either
continue through the parking lot, or return to where you came from via the
driveway.  A sign stares you in the face.

ExtraDescs.Description:
It reads, 
  "Vandals will be caned!  No exceptions!"
                   -The Management

rooms.Name: Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
You now stand in the south-west corner of the parking lot.  It looks
pretty much exactly like the rest of the parking lot.

rooms.Name: Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
This is the western side of the parking lot.  You look around you and see
extravagant wealth oozing out of the very air itself.  Why, even the ground
is...HEY LOOK!!!!!  YELLOW LINES ON THE PAVEMENT!!!  Wow, they really do
have it all here.

rooms.Name: Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
This is the eastern half of the parking lot.  There are cars here.  Ooooh, look
a Porsche, a Ferrari and a Lamborghini all parked side by side.  You really
feel like throwing up.

rooms.Name: Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
Will this blasted parking lot never end?!  You now stand in the northeast
corner of the lot.  You see Judge Smalls parking space but it has an ugly
brown car parked in it.  It's okay though, because it's currently being 
towed away.

rooms.Name: Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
Finally!  The parking lot ends here and a path for golf carts leads
north to the clubhouse.  The parking lot is south and east from here.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
The small paved pathway for the golf carts leads towards the counrty
club.  The path is well taken care of and has beautiful green grass on
either side of it.  Just beyond the grass are small flower beds with
colorful patches of flowers.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
As the path continues you see the large clubhouse in front of you.  The
birds sing as you make your way towards it.  The path widens slightly
and trees now run along either side of the path.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
You stand before the door to the clubhouse.  Inside, you can hear men who
are obviously drunk off their....well, they're a little tipsy...Anyway, 
there's alcohol inside, so what are you doing out here?

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description:
You now walk where only the rich and snobby normally tread.  The 19th
hole is north of here while the Pro Shop is south and east.

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description:
You walk down a hallway with pictures of the past presidents of the country
club along the walls.  They don't seem very happy considering how much money
they have.  To the north is the 19th hole and to the north and west is the bar.

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description:
You are still west of the pro shop and south of the door that leads
to the golf course.  Well, you can also get smashed north west of
here but that's neither here nor there. :>

rooms.Name: The Pro Shop
rooms.Description:
This is the mysterious pro shop.  It is rumored that people in hideously
ugly clothes come here to buy sticks to slap a little white ball around
in the yard.  Oh yeah, there are naked lady tees here too.

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description: You are still inside the clubhouse.  This place is getting kinda dull.

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description:
You are now standing in the middle of the clubhouse so as far as you
can tell, the world is currently revolving around you.  This place is
really good for your ego.

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description:
This is the north east corner of the clubhouse.  West of here is the door
out of this place.

rooms.Name: Inside the Clubhouse
rooms.Description:
You now stand in front of the door leading out to the golf course.  
Let's hit the links and kill some golfers.

rooms.Name: The 19th Hole
rooms.Description:
Welcome to the 19th Hole!  Belly up the bar and drink till you forget your
name.  As you head for a stool, the bartender says, "MEMBERS ONLY!!!"
Jeez, what a grouch.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
This small paved pathway runs north to the first set of tees.  It has a
small row of hedges running along the west side of the path and a pretty
flower bed on the easter side of it.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
Here you can follow the path north or take a different path to the east.
There is a sign here.

ExtraDescs.Description:
It reads:
  North:  #1 Tee
  East:   Golf Cart Parking Lot
  West:   Pool Area
Spray painted on the bottom is:
"BEWARE OF THE GOPHER!!!"

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
The sound of golf balls being hit and flying through the air can be heard to
the northwest of here.  The path heads west towards the pool and the first tee.

rooms.Name: Before the Golf Cart Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
The pathway ends here and brings you to the golf cart parking lot.  This is
where people usually meet after their pre-game drinks.  The sun shines down on
you as you continue.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
The path is now surrounded by a rows of trees in between the holes of the
golf course.  The first tees are to the north and the path back to the
clubhouse as well as the pool is to the south.

rooms.Name: Cart Path
rooms.Description:
Aaaah, what a BEAUTIFUL day!!  Birds are singing, the sun is shining,
golfers are screaming and cussing at little white balls all around you.
Life is good.  From here, you can travel into the front or back 9 of the
course.

rooms.Name: Golf Cart Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
You are now in the southwest corner of the golf cart parking lot.  A row of
small trees runs along the western edge of the parking lot with a small break
for a golf cart path.

rooms.Name: Golf Cart Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
You are in the southwest corner of the golf cart parking lot.  A small wooden
fence runs along the southern side of the parking lot.  Next to the fence is
an old beat up golf cart waiting to be repaired.

rooms.Name: Golf Cart Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
There are a few carts here in the back part of the golf cart parking lot.
To the north you can see the various holes of the golf course.  The path
to the first tee is to the west.

rooms.Name: Golf Cart Parking Lot
rooms.Description:
The golf cart parking lot is almost empty because it is prime time for
golf here at the country club.  The weather is clear and nice.  Perfect for
a nice relaxing . . ., well a round of golf at least.

rooms.Name: #1 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 5.  475 yds.
This is a fairly easy opening hole to get golfers warmed up.  It sinks
to a valley in the fairway and gently rises to the green.  No doglegs,
no sand, no water.  Like I said, easy.

rooms.Name: #1 Fairway
rooms.Description:
The fairway sinks into a valley here.  The grass, still wet from this
morning's watering, seems a little slippery.  The nearby trees also
provide shade for this section of the fairway.

rooms.Name: #1 Fairway
rooms.Description:
Here the fairway slowly slopes up toward the green.  The sun shines
through the trees creating all sorts of patterns.  You can not see the
green very easily from this position so you better go check it out before
you take your next shot.

rooms.Name: #1 Green
rooms.Description:
The grass on the green is darker than the grass of the fairway.  It is
also cut much shorter to allow for easier putting.  The cup is in the
western edge of the green so you better not hit the ball too hard.

rooms.Name: #2 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 3.  225 yds.
This is a long par 3 for the longer hitting golfers.  Good luck and try
to miss the sandtrap guarding the right side of the green.

rooms.Name: #2 Fairway
rooms.Description:
This fairway looks like all the others except there are huge furrows cris-
crossing it.  Hmmm...must be a BAD gopher problem around here.

rooms.Name: #2 Green
rooms.Description:
Yeek.  Even the green has been marked up by the little rodents.  It seems
that they could pay some professional to take care of this little problem.

rooms.Name: #3 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 5.  602 yds.
This is a long par 5 that curves around a water hole.  The entire fairway
is lined by a thick hedge to the south.  You can see the roof of the
caddyshack above the hedge.

rooms.Name: #3 Fairway
rooms.Description:
By the sound of music blaring and the screams of the partiers, it's
pretty obvious that you are getting very close to the caddyshack.
Kids these days have no respect for anything.  Just as that thought
crosses your mind, a beer bottle flies over the hedge and smashes
into a nearby tree.

rooms.Name: #3 Sand Trap
rooms.Description:
Well, here is where the comotion is loudest.  It looks like a path
has been worn down to the south directly into the hedge.

rooms.Name: #3 Fairway
rooms.Description:
At this point the fairway heads up to the green.  The cup is fairly easy
to spot and it looks like this will be an easy shot.  You line up your
club and swing!

rooms.Name: #3 Green
rooms.Description:
You come to the green of the third hole.  The green is sloped away from the
cup on the northwestern side.  It would be wise to take your time on this
shot because it might just roll all the way back to the sand trap.

rooms.Name: #4 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  375 yds.
This is a shorter par 4 to give you a break from the last hole.  The
fairway is flat as a pane of glass, except for the gopher trails here 
and there.

rooms.Name: #4 Fairway
rooms.Description:
The fairway extends for a few hundred yards toward the green.  The small
bumps in the fairway from where a gopher has been working can be seen.  It
looks like he has been busy.

rooms.Name: #4 Green
rooms.Description:
The green of the 4th hole is fairly small with the cup in the center of
it.  Like the fairway there is almost no slope, but it seems as though the
gopher decided to leave this section of the course alone.

rooms.Name: #5 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  365 yds.
This hole is a little more difficult than the last one because it has
a dogleg right just in front of the green.

rooms.Name: #5 Fairway
rooms.Description:
The fairway extends quite a distance before it makes a sharp turn right
before the green.  The leaves blow in the light wind as you scout out
your next shot.

rooms.Name: #5 Green
rooms.Description:
This small green is much longer than it is wide.  The green is almost
impossible to hit because of the sharp bend in the fairway just before
it.  The shot from the green is very easy, probably to make up for the
difficult fairway.

rooms.Name: #6 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 3.  155 yds.
This is the shortest hole on the course.  It should be an easy 6-iron or
lower club to the green.  Birdie this one and move on.

rooms.Name: #6 Green
rooms.Description:
This green is shaded by the many trees on either side of it.  Many people
mistake this green for an easy shot, but be carefull.  The ball tends to
hook to the left because of the slight slope to the green.

rooms.Name: #7 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  420 yds.
This is one of the longer par 4's on the course.  It has a straight
fairway before doglegging right just before the green.  If you get a 4
on this hole...count your blessings.

rooms.Name: #7 Fairway
rooms.Description:
You travel down a long fairway.  You start to decend into a small
valley which ends right before the green.  The grass is slightly taller here
for some unknown reason.

rooms.Name: #7 Fairway
rooms.Description:
The fairway bottoms out here at a small stream.  The fairway makes a
sharp climb to the southeast where the large green is.  It does not look
too bad at first, but then you realize that the slope is a little larger
than you thought.

rooms.Name: #7 Green
rooms.Description:
From the green of the 7th hole you get a nice view of the fairway behind
you.  It was quite a hike to get here, but it was worth it as you get
to put for one under par.

rooms.Name: #8 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  405 yds.
This is another decent length par 4.  Just make it through because the 
9th hole is what you've been waiting for.

rooms.Name: #8 Fairway
rooms.Description:
A long and fairly strait fairway lies in front of you.  It has a few hills,
but you have a strait shot to the green which is not too far away.  You take
aim and fire away!

rooms.Name: #8 Fairway
rooms.Description:
The fairway continues toward the green with only one small hill between
you and the cup.  It looks like a very easy shot so you just go for it.

rooms.Name: #8 Green
rooms.Description:
The long and narrow green of the 8th hols slopes slightly to the west.  Be
careful not to let it hook on you!  You take your time and then slowly pull
the club back.  You hit the ball. . . .it's going! . . .going! . . . .IN!!!

rooms.Name: #9 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  315 yds.
This is an extremely short par 4.  A birdie is very much a possibility on
this hole.  Finish up so we can get drunk before hole 10.

rooms.Name: #9 Fairway
rooms.Description:
The fairway bends slightly here.  Unfortunately your ball lands in 
between two gopher ruts.  Luckily you manage to hit it well enough
for it to land on the green.

rooms.Name: #9 Green
rooms.Description:
You have almost finished the front nine.  If you make this shot you will go
into the back nine under par.  This is a major accomplishment considering
all the gopher ruts.

rooms.Name: #10 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  385 yds.
This is a decent warm-up hole to get the blood flowing again.  Don't
get caught up by the easy look of this hole.   It can bite you.

rooms.Name: #10 Fairway
rooms.Description:
See?  I told you it could bite you.  Oh well, hopefully you can
make it up on the next few holes.

rooms.Name: #10 Green
rooms.Description:
Ack!  What is up with all of these gopher ruts?  You make a mental
note to complain to the management about the ruts when you get back
to the clubhouse.  You see the 11th tee to the northeast.

rooms.Name: #11 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 3.  195 yds.
How about something a little easier for your next hole?  This is a short
par 3 hole with nothing special about it.  Go to it.

rooms.Name: #11 Green
rooms.Description:
Wow!  Wasn't that an easy hole?  Why can't all of them be uncomplicated
like this hole was?  For some reason there aren't many gopher tracks
on this hole.

rooms.Name: #12 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 5.  515 yds.
This long, nasty hole has a huge dogleg left right in the middle of it.
This hole isn't very long but will challenge the best of golfers.  
Just when you thought you'd seen the last of the gophers, this hole is
marked up by their trails.  Hmmm...must be getting closer to their den.

rooms.Name: #12 Fairway
rooms.Description:
This hole looks like it is going to be very difficult.  Oh well,
you are still playing one of the best games of your life.  You
can see the fairway to the northeast.

rooms.Name: #12 Fairway
rooms.Description:
Isn't that just your luck?  Your ball has landed in a big gopher
rut.  You peer around to make sure noone is looking, and then kick
the ball out of the rut.  Hey, who will know?

rooms.Name: #12 Green
rooms.Description:
Ah, you finally made it to the green!  Unfortunately, there is a
gopher track directly between your ball and the hole.  You are
starting to wonder if the tracks will ever end.  As you are
progressing through the course, the tracks seem to get worse.

rooms.Name: #13 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  328 yds.
This goes back to the simpler holes of earlier in the course.  It's a 
par 4 with no doglegs in it.  You also notice that the gopher tracks are
getting worse.

rooms.Name: #13 Fairway
rooms.Description:
As you walk towards your ball, you fail to notice a gopher track
and fall on your butt.  You get up, curse out the grounds keeper,
and continue on your way.  The green is to the east.

rooms.Name: #13 Green
rooms.Description:
As you limp onto the green, you start to wish for an end to
this course.  Feeling a little foolish, you pray for the end
of the gopher tracks.

rooms.Name: #14 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 5.  485 yds.
This is a shorter par 5 but it curves around a small lake.  Don't get
nervous or your ball will surely hit the water.  I wouldn't say the gopher
tracks are getting worse or anything, but the fairway looks like a 
motocross track.

rooms.Name: #14 Fairway
rooms.Description:
You avoided the lake so far.  Unfortunately you did not miss the
shrubbery.  As you crawl into the bushes to find your ball, you
notice even more gopher tracks.  AUGH!  How many gophers _are_
there on this course?  The fairway continues to the west.

rooms.Name: #14 Fairway
rooms.Description:
You finally made it around the shrubbery and the lake.  You are
starting to wish that you had brought some Valium along.  Where
is a doctor when you really need him?

rooms.Name: #14 Green
rooms.Description:
Wow!  Your ball landed just a few inches away from the hole.  You
are apparently starting to calm down, because your game is getting
better.  Thankfully there were not many gopher tracks on this hole.

rooms.Name: #15 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 3.  200 yds.
This is a very short, very flat hole.  Well, flat that is except for the
dozens of gopher tracks marking up the fairway.

rooms.Name: #15 Green
rooms.Description:
Well, wasn't this an easy hole?  Unfortunately, the gopher tracks
made the hole a little harder for you.  The gopher tracks seem to
be getting worse as you progress through the course.

rooms.Name: #16 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  355 yds.
This hole is the worst you've seen on the course so far.  It is streaked
and marked and has holes in it all over the place.  Something REALLY needs
to be done about these gophers.

rooms.Name: #16 Fairway
rooms.Description:
Here is where the gopher tracks all seem to converge.  All of the tracks
seem to meet close to one spot here.  Maybe you'd better take a closer
look.

rooms.Name: #16 Green
rooms.Description:
There are quite a few gopher tracks on the green.  Thankfully the
tracks seem to be going towards the 16th fairway.  Hopefully you 
will not see any more tracks before you're done.  This hole looks
somewhat easier that the last hole.  You can see the 17th tee to
the west.

rooms.Name: #17 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  420 yds.
There are fewer gopher tracks here than there were on previous holes but
the hole is still pretty marked up.  Don't step in a hole and hurt yourself
because they're all over the place.

rooms.Name: #17 Fairway
rooms.Description:
This is a fairway, same as the others, with one distinction:  there is a
gaping hole in the middle of the fairway big enough to drop a semi through.
Looking down into it, the bottom is out of sight.  Better not go down there.

rooms.Name: #17 Green
rooms.Description:
Apparently the big hole on the fairway did not screw up your shot.
Wow, there are even a few gopher tracks on the green.  You would
think that the club would try to keep the course in a better shape
than this!  You are almost finished with the course.  The 18th tee
is to the west.  You can barely see the 19th hole.

rooms.Name: #18 Tee
rooms.Description:
Par 4.  335 yds.
This is an easy hole to finish up the course.  Let's hurry and finish
this hole so we can go get smashed at the 19th hole.

rooms.Name: #18 Fairway
rooms.Description:
It appears that Bishop Bickering didn't quite make it to the green
with his first try; he sliced it a little to the left.  Oh well, he
should have an easy time getting his ball onto the green since this
is one of the easiest holes on the course.  You can see the 19th
hole from here.  The 18th green is to the southwest.

rooms.Name: #18 Green
rooms.Description:
Yes!  You finally made it to the 18th green.  If you finish up quickly,
you can go into the clubhouse and have a few beers to celebrate your
game.  The cartpath can be seen to the southwest.

rooms.Name: Gravel Path
rooms.Description:
It's pretty obvious that this gravel path is used pretty often.  Many
bikes and motorcycles have frequented it.  Cigarette butts and beer
bottles lie scattered about.

rooms.Name: Before the Caddyshack
rooms.Description:
Here the path makes a sharp right and the true horror of the situation
becomes apparent.  These caddies have absolutely wrecked the place.  It
looks like a barbarian horde passed through here recently.

rooms.Name: Caddy Lounge Area
rooms.Description:
Never in your life have you seen such a waste of skin.  A dozen caddies
are lying around doing absolutely nothing but drinking and smoking pot.
It's pretty obvious that there was a fight here recently because the
gumball machine has been knocked over and its contents scattered every-
where.  The door to where Lou, the head Caddy, works is locked and no
one can find the key.

rooms.Name: Behind the Cage
rooms.Description:
The cage door is finally open and Lou is free to go.  Even in his weakened
condition he thinks that you are here to steal his money.  You'd better
leave before you piss him off.

rooms.Name: A Dark Hole
rooms.Description:
As you crawl down the hole, you realize that you are going to need
some light.  Fumbling through your pockets, you find your little
flashlight that is attached to your keychain.  After turning the
flashlight on, you notice that the tracks lead to the north.  Are
you sure you want to find out where these tracks lead?

rooms.Name: The Tunnel Widens
rooms.Description:
Well, your knees stopped shaking long enough for you to follow the
tracks into this room.  You hear some strange sounds coming from
the east.  Could you be close to finding out where these tracks lead?

rooms.Name: The Den
rooms.Description:
You found out where those tracks led... into a gopher's den!  As
you look at the gopher, you get an eerie feeling.  This gopher
does not look very friendly.  You better leave its den unless you
want to find out how mean the gopher can get.

rooms.Name: The Deep Hole
rooms.Description:
You have fallen down into a very very deep hole.  Also, you have stumbled
into one of the most obvious death traps ever designed.  Just as you
feel your face flush with embarrassment, 3 gophers poke their heads 
through the dirt and laugh at you.  Don't you feel rotten?

rooms.Name: The Pool
rooms.Description:
Well, this place WOULD be a great place to swim if there were any water.
The pool was drained because there was a...well, something in the pool that
we won't get into.

rooms.Name: Quaint wedding chapel in the hills.
rooms.Description:
You now stand in a small wedding chapel nestled in between the rolling
hills of a distant land.  The small chamber is lined with pews that are
strewn with lace and white ribbons down the aisle.  A stained glass window
allows the sun's rays into the chapel and makes the room dance with color
so beautiful that your heart sings with joy.
